overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, aiming to validate its adherence to the provided Statement of
  Work and detailed questionnaire specification. The agent performed an in-depth
  analysis, identifying several critical gaps and missing features.
  Subsequently, the agent systematically addressed these deficiencies. Key
  implementations included adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with
  associated safety warnings, integrating detection and reporting for COMISA and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and enhancing the report with relevant outbound
  links to professional resources. The agent also refined the Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness (EDS) scoring to incorporate weighted criteria and significantly
  expanded the CSV export functionality to capture all questionnaire data.
  Furthermore, new questions were introduced to screen for pain severity and
  chronic fatigue symptoms, providing a more holistic assessment. The approach
  involved meticulous updates across data types, validation schemas, user
  interface components, and server-side logic for report and data generation.
